data.description: OPEN HOUSE Saturday (12/23) from 12-2pm!Celebrate the new year in this tranquil basement ranch wrapped in brick with mountain views on a level 0.76-acre lot complete with a gorgeous lawn, covered/screened rear deck, and several recent updates! Its turnkey and ready for you to be its new owner! As you approach this Maryville subdivision and home, you'll be enamored by the panoramic mountain views of the foothills and beautiful country setting that backs to Lambert Acres Golf Club. This well maintained home is ready! Updates performed by the seller include: new roof with 50 YEAR architectural shingles (2021), new HVAC (2020), new tiled master shower with glass door (2023), epoxy garage floor (2021), new double-sided insulated garage door (2023), new water heater (2022), new gutters with leaf blaster guards (2021), converted spiral staircase to traditional staircase leading to basement (2020), septic system serviced (2021), Radon system (2021), and new pantry doors (2023). As you approach the home you'll notice the beautiful brick, hardscaping, and craftsman shutters. Entering the home, you'll find hardwood floors spilling into the spacious family room that flows out to the private covered/screened back deck. The family room features a tray ceiling and fireplace. The large kitchen has several cabinets, pantry, tiled floors, and an oversized passthrough looking into the family room. The dining room is wrapped in windows. The floor plan is highly desireable with master bedroom on the main and spare bedrooms across the living area. This home has great flow! The spacious primary bedroom boasts a tray ceiling and his/her walk-in closets with the ensuite featuring a brand-new tiled shower and his/her vanities. Both bathrooms are protected by tile flooring. The huge open basement could double as a man cave, bonus area, bedroom, or crafts workshop and features a wet bar and storage room great for your canning project or safe room with convenient access to the kitchen upstairs. The basement has an additional garage for your extra car, boat, hobby items, or could serve as a great workshop leading out to the backyard. The 2-car garage on the main level boasts a newer epoxy floor and extra storage room with two huge windows for natural lighting. This awesome home has affordable annual expenses with NO HOA, county-only taxes, and septic system! Convenient location tucked between the Smokies and shopping in Maryville! Book your showing today!
